Regional policy and planning. Principles of networking. Development of cooperation networks.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing students with skills for building collaboration networks while considering regional circumstances. Also, the course allows for developing skills necessary for participating in international cooperation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) know the most important regional problems and their adjustment policies; 2) know the principles of networking (and create opportunities for networking); 3) analyse data and create networks that meet respective needs; 4) make proposals for the development of networks at the local and national level; 5) know international organisations and networks operating in the field of social work and be motivated to participate in their activities.
